# Code Style Guidelines

Follow these code style conventions:

- Use early returns for improved readability
- Use Tailwind classes exclusively, avoid raw CSS
- Prefer "class:" over ternary operators in class attributes
- Use descriptive names with "handle" prefix for event handlers
- Implement proper accessibility features
- Use const arrow functions with TypeScript types
- Use function keyword for pure functions
- Write declarative JSX
- Avoid unnecessary curly braces in conditionals 